Palaeoenvironment and depositional setting.
The Gram Formation was deposited in a marine environment at a depth between 50 and 100 m, as indicated by the marine flora associated with terrestrial material, foraminifera and the marine fauna (
Rasmussen, 1958
, 
1966
; 
Laursen & Kristofferson, 1999
; 
Dybkjaer & Piasecki, 2010
). Fine-grained storm beds similar to the extant coastal layers in the North Sea suggest a progradation of the shoreline (
Rasmussen, 2005
).

